First Granite Bancorp Incsaid it agreed in principle to become a wholly owned subsidiaryof Magna Group Inc &lt;MAGI>.    Under terms of the agreement, First Granite shareholderswill receive 2.175 shares of Magna for each First Granite shareheld. First Granite shareholders will be asked to approve thetranaction in late summer.    First Granite, which has 675,000 shares outstanding, as ofDec 31, 1986 had assets of 186.5 mln dlrs. It owns FirstGranite City National Bank and Colonial Bank of Granite City,Ill.    Magna Groups as of Dec 31, 1986 had assets of 1.47 billiondlrs. It owns 13 banks, a data services company, a mortgagecompany and a trust company, serving St. Louis as well asSpringfield, Centralia and Decatur, Ill. Reuter&#3;